    =((A1-A2)*86400000+11644473600000)*10000

Where:&lt;br/&gt;
A1 is your date, like 10/5/2019.&lt;br/&gt;
A2 is the date 1/1/1970.&lt;br/&gt;
86400000 is number of milliseconds on 1 day.&lt;br/&gt;
11644473600000 is number of milliseconds between 1/1/1601 and 1/1/1970.&lt;br/&gt;
10000 to make it 18 digit.

